The National Primary Health Care Development Agency (NPHCDA) has revealed that 73,465 Nigerians have received their 2nd dose of Oxford/Astrazeneca vaccine and over 1.9million of targeted eligible Nigerians have been vaccinated with their first dose.  The Executive Director, NPHCDA Dr. Faisal Shuaib who made this known today as the agency gives update on Covid 19 vaccination in Abuja, called all Nigerians who have received their first dose to check their vaccination cards for the date of their second dose and proceed to the same health facility where they got their first jab, to ensure full protection against COVID-19.  Dr Faisal Shuaib said there have been cases of mild, moderate, and severe Adverse Events Following Immunization (AEFI) since the agency officially rolled out Covid-19 vaccination on March 15, 2021, with 86 cases of moderate to severe incidents all fully recovered.  In his remarks the World Health Organization Country Rep. Dr Walter Kazadi said amongst most of the strategies WHO is advocating for in terms of minimizing the risk of loosing the vaccines comes from Nigeria because of her outstanding performance.